The paper focuses on trajectory prediction for robots and autonomous vehicles, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach is data-driven and uses neural networks, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sensor input, which could indicate a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the challenges of modeling complex traffic and dynamic uncertainties, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
